1765

Datum in cancellaria nostra de KAERDIFF sub sigillo cancellarie nostre ibidem pen[ultimo die] Aprilis anno regni nostri post conquestum decimo octavo. The King’s seal for the chancery of Oardjff ; but imperfect.

Endorsed—-‘ A patent of Kinge Hy. to one Howell of certan londes in Dodlaud’

The King here appears as Lord of Glamorgan and Morgan.

Dodland is unknown, but the other places named lie probably between Nash and Sully. Howell must be the grandson of the preceding Howell Carne.

There is considerable difficulty with this Charter, which has intimate connection with No. MOOOXXVH. Both are dated penult. April, 18 Henry, but while this appears at one time to have borne the endorsement of ‘ Henry VII.,’ the other bears that of ‘ Henry VIII.y Probably these endorsements are not contemporary, and one or other is erroneous. The British Museum Cataloyue qs Scala attributes this to Henry VII.⁷ but the Index Locorum to Henry VIII. It is difficule to decide.

MOOLXXV.

[MARGAM CHARTER] 5 JULY. 18 ΗΕΝ. VII. 1503.

Pateat universis per presentes me RES ap Tnoms ap RES remisisse relaxasse et omnino pro me et heredibus meis imperpetuum quietum clamasse J EUAN ap [MORGAN ap] LLEWELIN ap MORGAN heredibus suis et assignatis totum jus titulum et clameum juris que umquam habeo habui seu quovismodo habere potero de et in duobus tenementis cum omnibus suis pertinentiis prout jacent in dominio de AVENE per antiquas metas et bundas videlicet inter Commo VAUR et Commo VECHAN. Habendum et tenendum duo predicta tenementa cum omnibus suis pertinentiis prefato J EUAN heredibus et assignatis suis imperpetuum de capitali domino feodi illius per redditus et servicia prius inde debita et de jure consueta. seu nomine meo aliquod jus titulum seu clameum juris de et in duobus predictis
